% Khoros helpfile follows below:
%
%  PROGRAM
% ccompressROI - Eliminate masked points in ROI making single row object
%
%  DESCRIPTION
% This program eliminates all points in the input object (specified with the [-i] parameter) that are masked as non-valid, reproducing only the valid points in the output object (specified with the [-o] parameter). This is useful for some routines that scans the input data set several times, for example, the trainer for the Back-Propagation Neural Network classifier, because masks often slow down these routines. 
% The dimensions of the object are changed - regardless of the input object dimensions, if in the input object there are V points that are masked as valid, i.e. with masks different of 0, these points will be joined in a single-row object with dimensions Vx1x1x1xE where E is the element dimension (the program processes the H,W,D and T dimensions, extracting valid vectors from it).
% If the input object has no mask and dimensions WxHxDxTxE, the output object will have dimensions (W*H*D*T)x1x1x1xE.
% The side effect is that the original spatial information cannot be preserved on the output object - this program should \fBnot" be used if spatial information is important for further processing steps.
%
%  
%
%  EXAMPLES
% All examples for the Classify toolbox are listed on the Classify Toolbox Manual. There aren't specific examples for this routine yet, but the cbpnn_signature pane is actually a call for it. There is an example of the  cbpnn_signature kroutine in the example workspace Classify:workspaces:BPNN-Image.
%
%  "SEE ALSO"
% cbpnn_signature, cROIfromcoords.
%
%  RESTRICTIONS 
% This program should \fBnot" be used if spatial information is important for further processing steps.
%
%  REFERENCES 
